<chapter id="whats_new">
	<title>What's new</title>
    
    <simplesect>
        <title>What's new in 1.5.0</title>
        <para>
            <emphasis role="strong">Eclipse 3.5 Galileo dependencies</emphasis>
        </para>
        <para>
            Apache Directory Studio now uses the latest and greatest Eclipse 3.5 Galileo dependencies.            
        </para>
    </simplesect>
	
	<simplesect>
		<title>What's new in 1.4.0</title>
		<para>
			<emphasis role="strong">Internationalization</emphasis>
		</para>
		<para>
			Apache Directory Studio is now fully internationalized.
			Out of the box English, French and German translations are provided.			
		</para>
		<para>
			<screenshot>
				<mediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata scale="50"
							fileref="images/whats_new_internationalization.png" format="PNG" />
					</imageobject>
				</mediaobject>
			</screenshot>
		</para>
	</simplesect>

	<simplesect>
		<title>What's new in 1.2.0</title>
		<para>
			<emphasis role="strong">
				New Save and Print actions
			</emphasis>
		</para>
		<para>
			Two new actions have been added to the main toolbar of
			Apache Directory Studio: Save and Print actions.
		</para>
		<para>
			<screenshot>
				<mediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata scale="50"
							fileref="images/whats_new_save_print_actions.png" format="PNG" />
					</imageobject>
				</mediaobject>
			</screenshot>
		</para>
		<para>
			<emphasis role="strong">
				Network Connections preference page
			</emphasis>
		</para>
		<para>
			The Network Connections preference page from Eclipse has
			been added to Apache Directory Studio. This page allows the
			user to set up its network connection settings, such as
			direct connection or proxy configuration (HTTP, SSL, SOCKS
			Proxy).
		</para>
		<para>
			<screenshot>
				<mediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata scale="50"
							fileref="images/whats_new_network_connections_pref.png" format="PNG" />
					</imageobject>
				</mediaobject>
			</screenshot>
		</para>
	</simplesect>

</chapter>